article.headline: Northwestern 77, UMKC 62
article.story: EVANSTON, Ill. -- Kevin Coble scored 16 of his 22 points in the second half, including four three-pointers, as Northwestern defeated Missouri-Kansas City 77-62 on Monday. Freshman John Shurna added 20 points and Michael Thompson 17 for Northwestern (7-1). UMKC (4-8) missed its first nine shots from the field. The Wildcats built as much as an 11-point first half lead (23-12), before settling for a 32-23 advantage. The Kangaroos cut its deficit to 37-31 early in the second half, but Northwestern went on a 9-0 run to seize control at 46-31. Each time the Kangaroos tried to mount a comeback Coble answered, scoring 13 straight points for Northwestern. Coble finished the game 9-16 from the field, including 4-7 from 3-point range. Spencer Johnson led UMKC with 22 points and a game-high 12 rebounds. Dane Brumagin scored 14 points and Fred Ford and Reggie Hamilton each had 12 points.
